<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-07-0731 </DOCNO><TEXT>The following report describes the result of a two-and-a-half trimesterproject group study on the theme 'legal and operational problems of publicutilities'. Following several introductory remarks, the following topicsare treated in sections: Legal forms and structures, organization oftariffs, supply and usage dictates as well as connection and supply obligations,modalities in accountancy and powers of enforcement, hability in casesof damage and decision processes of public enterprises in the politicalfield of force.</TEXT></DOC>